div.p:
"According to the laws and constitution of the people, which I have suffered to be established,
and should be maintained for the rights and protection of all flesh, according to just and holy
principles;

"Therefore, I, the Lord, justify you, and your brethren of my church, in befriending that law
which is the constitutional law of the land [the test of its constitutionality in the words of the
Lord here is whether it preserves man's agency];
